"Oh, I do hope not, I really do hope not. Pulling together is the aim of despotism and tyranny. Free men pull in all kinds of directions."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugizzit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gizzit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/01 3:02:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Save a good EQ website</span><hr size=1> <br>
I liked EQ Maps, it was a good site - I especially liked their item database - but.......<br>
<br>
Between all the sites that are asking for voluntary donations, and the sites which are starting to demand payment, how much could you end up spending on this game and associated information?<br>
<br>
I know that ultimately there are huge overheads to meet, and that banner advertising just didn't work, but it just means that I (and many like me) will have to be more selective about sites to visit.  Of course you will get the asses who try to &quot;beat the system&quot;, or those who subscribe once for an entire guild - but as Kezzek said - that just compounds the problem.<br>
<br>
Some sites will go under - I am truly sorry about that - it is sad to see so much enthusiasm and energy come to naught.<br>
<br>
I do find it disturbing however, that sites which have been built around contributions from players are now being forced to charge those players to view their own contributions.<br>
<br>
