 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/01 8:02:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Save a good EQ website</span><hr size=1> true, we can't start paying for everything.....but I just like eqmaps.com so much, it's the best site I have for item information, and the maps help when eqatlas.com doesn't have one.<br>
<br>
question is, how many sites do you really use? when I look thru my bookmarks the ones I really need are eqmaps.com eqatlas.com and the safehouse, 3 sites. not that much. we'll see how it goes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udimuyensylvanesty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dimuyen Sylvanesty</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/01 11:48:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Save a good EQ website</span><hr size=1> Well I hope that now that he's charging for subscriptions that he at least gives map writers free access, or that he pays them.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitewhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitewhisper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/01 11:39:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Save a good EQ website</span><hr size=1> I have not seen this posted/ I hope most of you realize that about 80% if not more of the EQ message boards for your favorite class are using EZboard. Most of the server populations have also migrated at one time or another to an EZboard forum. I did some research today to come to this number be hitting a lot of the class specific message boards from their websites. I ended up on EZboard most of the time.<br>
<br>
Supporting EZboard will support and preserve a vast knowledge base of EQ information. I could not say this about any other message board system. I know for a fact that Rogues (The Safehouse), Magicians (The Magicians Tower), Monks (no special name) and Druids (The Druids Grove) all use EZboard as their primary message board service. So whether or not you use one of these fine informational pools you will actually contribute to saving them all. Each has a wonderful array of posters who know and post very detailed and valuable information on EZboard.<br>
<br>
Many of the servers have EZboard forums as well as a large number of guilds. You should keep all this in mind when trying to decide if it is worth it or not. You may be surprised one day to find a great new website that moves you to an EZboard forum for their message base. I cannot count the number of EZboards I have hit this way in and out of EQ information. <br>
<br>
I am not trying to say you should contribute. I only wanted to detail a few facts about how EQ message boards and EZboard are heavily integrated at this point in time. It is a free choice but a somewhat serious one. We are all faced with what do we want to keep seeing and what was just additional distractions. Do what you feel is right for you! I will be applying for a gold membership early next week for my guild's site since I value this service as one of the best message board services I have seen. If we help in survive it will once again grow and flourish as it has in the past.<br>
<br>
Just my two copper but no one else had really stated this.<br>
<br>
Whitewhisper Brightfist<br>
Long winded monk of Norrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessage?topicID=2205.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessage?topicID=2225.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.emailToFriend?topicID=2206.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.threadControl?topicID=2206.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2206.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2206.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehouset